ited Kingdom, and elsewhere—Monty Python's Flying Circus, Key and Peele, Saturday Night Live, Airplane!, and Smack the Pony—Clayton reveals the techniques and resonances of humor.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aComedy sketchesxHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 0aComedyxHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 0aComedy-History and criticism. 4aAmerican Studies : American Culture. 4aAmerican Studies : American Studies. 4aArea Studies : British Studies. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2020z978311149149340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438478302423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438478302/original  a978-3-11-149149-3  SUNY Press eBook Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles